    "For instance, DSCs in Western Europe may devote more resources towards mitigating foreign disinformation around elections, while DSCs in Eastern Europe might prioritize e.g., monitoring domestic disinformation around social issues [65, 66, 85].",
    "Analyzing interactions between national DSCs and VLOPs can also surface crucial nuances in oversight approaches across Member States' sociopolitical contexts.",
    "This specificity necessitates caution in making broad generalizations; yet, analyses can inform coordinated efforts towards harmonization of responsibilities under the DSA across diverse environments through: • Systematized sharing of oversight techniques and campaign responses between national Digital Service Coordinators to highlight best practices through the European Board for Digital Services.",
    "• Paired auditing and interview studies simultaneously assessing platform and DSC adaptation across Member States to highlight inconsistencies.Instead, comparative research highlighting differential manifestations and impacts of disinformation, as well as variations in platforms' responses, will be essential to account for key distinctions across services and countries [141,162].Obtaining Research Data Obtaining adequate access to platform data represents a major constraint, as transparency provisions in the DSA grant only limited data sharing with researchers (Articles 31 and 40).",
